<tool name="edit_code_evaluator_draft">
  <description>Propose edits to the open code-evaluator draft. The browser renders an inline diff and the user accepts or rejects it — this tool does not change the form immediately.</description>
  <when_to_use>
    - The user asks to modify the draft's source code, name, description, language, sandbox selection, or input mapping.
    - You want to suggest a concrete change rather than describing it in chat.
  </when_to_use>
  <preflight>
    - Always call `read_code_evaluator_draft` first to obtain the latest `revision`.
    - Pass that `revision` back as `expectedRevision`. If the draft changed since the read, the edit is rejected; re-read and retry.
  </preflight>
  <operations>
    - `operations` must always be an array, even for a single edit. Operations apply in order.
    - Use camelCase field names exactly as shown.
    - Common shapes:
      - `{"type":"set_source_code","sourceCode":"def evaluate(output):\n    return 1.0"}`
      - `{"type":"set_language","language":"PYTHON"}` — only valid in `create` mode.
      - `{"type":"set_sandbox_config","sandboxConfigId":"U2FuZGJveENvbmZpZzox"}` — pass `null` to clear. The sandbox config's language must match the draft language.
      - `{"type":"set_input_mapping","inputMapping":{"pathMapping":{"input":"attributes.input.value"},"literalMapping":{}}}`
      - `{"type":"set_description","description":"Scores hallucination risk"}`
      - `{"type":"set_name","name":"hallucination-v2"}`
      - `{"type":"set_output_configs","outputConfigs":[{"kind":"freeform","name":"hallucination-v2","optimizationDirection":"MAXIMIZE","threshold":0.5,"lowerBound":0,"upperBound":1}]}` — whole-list replace. Other valid `kind`s: `classification` (with a `values` list of `{label, score?}`) and `continuous` (with `lowerBound`/`upperBound`). Use the draft evaluator name on each entry unless the evaluator clearly returns multiple independent outputs. Propose output configs whenever you can infer them from the source rather than leaving the draft's defaults in place.
  </operations>
  <invariants>
    - Never rename or remove the `evaluate` function. The runtime calls it by name.
    - Only declare parameters from `{input, output, reference, metadata}` on `evaluate` — additional parameters will fail at execution.
    - In `edit` mode, `set_language` is rejected (language is immutable post-create).
    - In `create` mode, switching `set_language` may clear an incompatible `sandbox_config_id`; suggest a compatible one in a follow-up turn if needed.
  </invariants>
  <sandbox_config>
    - When emitting `set_sandbox_config`, pick `sandboxConfigId` from `<available_sandbox_configs>` below. Do NOT invent or guess an ID, and do NOT issue a `sandboxProviders` GraphQL query — the inventory below is authoritative for this turn.
    - The chosen config's `language` must match the draft language; in `create` mode after `set_language`, re-check the inventory for a compatible entry.
{% if available_sandbox_configs %}
    <available_sandbox_configs>
{% for cfg in available_sandbox_configs %}
      <config id="{{ cfg.sandbox_config_id | sanitize(enclosing_tag="available_sandbox_configs", max_chars=128) | e }}" name="{{ cfg.name | sanitize(enclosing_tag="available_sandbox_configs", max_chars=128) | e }}" language="{{ cfg.language | e }}">
        <internet_access setting="{{ cfg.internet_access | e }}" backend_capability="{{ cfg.internet_access_mode | e }}"/>
        <dependencies supported="{{ 'true' if cfg.supports_dependencies else 'false' }}">
{% for pkg in cfg.dependencies %}
          <package>{{ pkg | sanitize(enclosing_tag="package", max_chars=256) | e }}</package>
{% endfor %}
        </dependencies>
        <env_vars supported="{{ 'true' if cfg.supports_env_vars else 'false' }}">
{% for name in cfg.env_var_names %}
          <name>{{ name | sanitize(enclosing_tag="name", max_chars=128) | e }}</name>
{% endfor %}
        </env_vars>
      </config>
{% endfor %}
    </available_sandbox_configs>
{% else %}
    <available_sandbox_configs/>
{% endif %}
  </sandbox_config>
  <guidelines>
    - Emit operations ONLY for fields you intend to change. If a field already has the value you want, do not include an op for it — redundant ops produce noisy diff previews and waste tokens.
    - Keep edits small and focused so the user can read the diff. Group related field changes together when they form one logical intent.
    - After proposing the edit, briefly summarize what the diff will show so the user knows what they are accepting or rejecting.
  </guidelines>
</tool>
